IBADAN – The new candidate of the All Progressive Congress, APC, representing Ibadan Southwest II State Constituency at the State House of Assembly, Aare Akogun Idris Ajimobi, as described the emergence of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu as the presidential flag bearer of the All progressive congress, APC in the next general elections as the unsurpassable for the party. He stated this while reacting to the outcome of the Special APC Convention which produced Tinubu as the Party’s candidate. Aare Akogun Ajimobi who described Tinubu as a Peace Advocate and development Agent noted that his emergence spelt more fortunes for the party and the country at large. The lawmaker to be hopeful explained that Tinubu’s track records in the past when he was governor of Lagos state, the achievement and success recorded then in Lagos state, placing Lagos State on a pace setter and one of the leading economies in Nigeria and Africa at large. “He said no doubt in my mind cause Asiwaju won’t disappoint and he won’t let Nigerians down when it comes to Peace and development due to his style of leadership in the past” Idris Ajimobi also noted that Tinubu was a good match for the candidate of the People’s Democratic Party, expressing confidence that he would be the eventual winner come 2023. He however congratulated Ahmed Tinubu for the feat achieved.